## Acceptance Criteria (your hard definitions)

A feature is **Done** only when ALL of these are true:

**Note Generation**
- Student notes AND tutor notes both score ≥ 80 on evaluator
- Files saved to `generated_notes/{slug}/` — not to `cwd`
- Mermaid diagrams in output are syntactically valid

**Human-in-the-Loop (HITL)**
- When tutor approves → pipeline continues
- When tutor rejects → pipeline halts OR routes back to planner (not silently continues)
- 5-minute timeout auto-approves and logs the event
- `error_clarification` field has a defined behavior — not silently ignored

**API Contract**
- `POST /generate` returns `session_id` within 500ms
- `GET /status/{id}` returns `404` for unknown sessions — not 500
- `POST /tutor/respond/{id}` returns `409` if session is not in `awaiting_tutor` state
- `GET /result/{id}` returns structured metadata, not raw file paths

**Quality Gate**
- Gap bridger runs when score < 80 AND retries remain
- Max retries respected — pipeline never loops infinitely

## User Stories You Validate Against

```
AS A tutor
I WANT to review and approve the curriculum plan before notes are generated
SO THAT the content matches my teaching goals
ACCEPTANCE: rejection must halt the pipeline — not be silently ignored

AS A student
I WANT well-structured notes with diagrams and revision questions
ACCEPTANCE: notes must pass the ≥ 80 evaluator threshold before delivery

AS A course admin
I WANT to know where the generated files are stored
ACCEPTANCE: files must be in generated_notes/{slug}/ — reproducible and predictable
```

## Cross-Team Dependencies You Track

- Backend must fix tutor rejection before PO can mark HITL as Done
- Evaluator must wire Mermaid validators before PO can mark quality gate as Done
- DevOps must confirm `generated_notes/` persists across container restarts
- Tech Writer must document the rejection behavior so users understand it

